Package: cuems-gradient-motiond
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends},
         ${misc:Depends},
         cuems-common
Description: CUEMS Gradient Motion Engine (fade-engine daemon)
 gradient-motiond drives parametric volume/opacity envelopes for the CUEMS
 cue playback system. Receives start_fade/cancel_motion/cancel_all/start_crossfade
 commands over an NNG bus from the CUEMS controller engine, evaluates the
 sigmoidal/linear/exponential/logarithmic curves locked to MIDI Time Code,
 and emits OSC value updates to audio (cuems-audioplayer /volmaster) and
 video (cuems-videocomposer /videocomposer/layer/{id}/opacity) players.
 .
 The systemd unit cuems-gradient-motiond.service is shipped by the
 cuems-common package; this package only installs the binary at
 /usr/bin/gradient-motiond.
